  "text": "Experiment 1 in [CITATION_1] is a replication of [CITATION_2] in that a notion of task difficulty is modified by making T1 more or less frequent. As discussed in the previous section, we argue that the relationship between task difficulty and frequency is unclear. What is clear is that frequency alone is a potent factor in determining P3 size [CITATION_3] , which explains a larger P3 for infrequent targets than for frequent targets (Figure 1 in [CITATION_4] without resorting to the explanations involving task difficulty or resource allocation.",
